Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle from a probably Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; little mica, white inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and prow symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 4 or 132, 19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0249)
